   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">All systems must be fitted with either:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Internal backfeed protection</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">External backfeed protection</p>
               </li>
            </ul>The internal backfeed protection is an option that can be selected.<note class="- topic/note ">If selected, the internal backfeed protection is shown in the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Single Line Diagram</i> for the system.</note>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">Backfeed protection
helps to prevent the occurrence of any hazardous voltages at the AC
supply terminals in the case of an AC mains failure due to unexpected
backfeed from the inverter operating in stored energy mode.</p>
